://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Jack-Nicholson-picture-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jack-nicholson">杰克·尼科尔森（Jack Nicholson）</a>在<a href="https://www.nme.com/series/saturday-night-live"><em>《星期六夜现场》（Saturday Night Live）</em></a>成立50周年庆典情节中罕见的公开露面，构成了现场人群的一部分，并介绍了其中一场。</p><p>表演传奇人物在观众中出现在观众中，他介绍了一位前<em>SNL</em>演员时说：“女士们，先生们，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/adam-sandler">亚当·桑德勒</a>！”桑德勒（Sandler）带领一群兴奋的人群说：“让我们听听杰克宝贝（Jack Baby）！杰克今晚做了！爱你兄弟”。两人一起出现在2003年喜剧<em>《愤怒管理》</em>中。</p><p>杰克·尼科尔森（Jack Nicholson）是好莱坞最著名的明星之一，以其在电影经典中的作品而闻名，例如<em>《闪亮》，《唐人街》，《好人》</em> ，以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/tim-burton">蒂姆·伯顿（Tim Burton）</a> 1989年版的<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/batman"><em>《蝙蝠侠》（Batman）</em></a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/films/joker">小丑</a>。他是<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/oscars">奥斯卡颁奖</a>典礼上最受提名的男演员，共有12项提名。</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">杰克·尼科尔森（Jack Nicholson）在<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/SNL50?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">＃SNL50</a>中出人意料地介绍了亚当·桑德勒（Adam Sandler）。<br /> <a href="https://t.co/iN3IIuOaEb">pic.twitter.com/in3iiuoaaeb</a></p><p> - 电影更新（@filmupdates） <a href="https://twitter.com/FilmUpdates/status/1891326878922764620?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2025年2月17日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>自2010年以来<em>，</em>这位明星就没有在大屏幕上表现出来，自从奥斯卡奖得主退休以来的几年中出现了报道。尼科尔森（Nicholson）从未正式确认这一点，尽管他在2013年的<em><a href="https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2013/09/jack-nicholson-retirement-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener">虚荣博览会</a></em>采访中确实说明他不再被“再来”。</p><p> In 2023, podcaster <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/jack-nicholson-rather-sit-under-tree-read-book-than-return-acting-3534775">Marc Maron said during an episode of his show</a> : “A friend of mine wanted to put him in a movie, and he had a conversation with him. But Jack says, &#39;I don&#39;t want to do it.&#39; He goes, &#39;You know what I did today? I sat under a tree and I read a book.&#39;” His guest on the show, producer Lou Adler, a friend of Nicholson&#39;s confirmed: “That sounds like Jack”.</p><p> Conversely, last July actress and Nicholson&#39;s former partner Lara Flynn Boyle <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/jack-nicholsons-ex-partner-says-hes-never-retired-3771849">appeared to debunk the rumours</a> , saying in an interview: “The world of Jack is always here. There&#39;s no retiring for the world of Jack.绝不”。 In January <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/first-new-photograph-of-jack-nicholson-in-almost-two-years-emerges-3826101">, the first public pictures of him in almost two years emerged</a> via a social media post from his daughter Lorraine.</p><p> Nicholson was not the only famous face making their first appearance in some time.<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/aubrey-plaza">奥布里广场（Aubrey Plaza）</a>引入了音乐表演， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/aubrey-plaza-makes-first-appearance-since-husbands-death-at-snl50-3838623">自从丈夫杰夫·巴纳（Jeff Baena）于一月份去世以来，这是第一次出现在摄像头上。</a></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/jack-nicholson-makes-rare-public-appearance-for-snl50-special-3838710">Jack Nicholson makes rare public appearance for &#39;SNL50&#39; special</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 Jameela Jamil关于她如何“毁了” Glastonbury的Coldplay Superfan Benedict Cumberbatch https://www.nme.com/news/music/jameela-jamil-on-how-she-ruined-glastonbury-for-coldplay-superfan-benedict-cumberbatch-3838706?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=jameela-jamil-on-how-she-ruined-glastonbury-for-coldplay-superfan-benedict-cumberbatchLiberty Dunworth Mon, 17 Feb 2025 16:43:31 +0000 Music NewsNewsTV News..Let’s Talk – mental healthhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3838706 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Chris Martin of Coldplay, Jameela Jamil and Benedict Cumberbatch" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “He&#39;s trying to listen to the song, and I&#39;m just going &#39;ughhhhh!&#39;”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jameela-jamil-on-how-she-ruined-glastonbury-for-coldplay-superfan-benedict-cumberbatch-3838706">Jameela Jamil on how she “ruined” Glastonbury for Coldplay superfan Benedict Cumberbatch</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Chris Martin of Coldplay, Jameela Jamil and Benedict Cumberbatch" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/coldplay-Jamil-Cumberbatch@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Jameela Jamil has recalled the time she “ruined” <a href="https://www.nme.com/glastonbury-2025">Glastonbury</a> for <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/benedict-cumberbatch">Benedict Cumberbatch</a> .</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/coldplay-glastonbury-2024-live-review-photos-setlist-3770486">Coldplay live at Glastonbury 2024: Worthy Farm&#39;s house band become “100,004 people” strong</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p> The former star of <em>The Good Place</em> and mental health advocate shared the anecdote during a new interview with <a href="/artists/paloma-faith">Paloma Faith</a> , as part of a new episode for the latter&#39;s <em>Mad Sad Bad</em> podcast.</p><p> During the discussion, Jamil explained some of the hardships she has faced in recent times, and shared that the 2024 edition of Glastonbury came during “one of the saddest” times of her life. This, she recalled, was because of the unexpected and “sudden” death of a friend.</p><p> While at the Worthy Farm event, Jamil was still in a vulnerable state and found herself getting emotional during <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/coldplay">Coldplay</a> &#39;s massive headline set on the Pyramid Stage. This, she recalled, took place while she was next to <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/marvel">MCU</a> actor Benedict Cumberbatch.</p><p> “Now I&#39;ve become someone who cries to &#39;Fix You&#39; by Coldplay,” Jamil recalled. “我在格拉斯顿伯里（Glastonbury）无法控制。 And I was ruining it for Benedict Cumberbatch who was next to me – who I don&#39;t know.”</p><p> “So he&#39;s just trying to listen to the song, and I&#39;m just going – &#39;ughhhhh!&#39;” </p><p><iframe title="Spotify Embed: Jameela Jamil: I Love Being Invisible To Men" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="152" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/4lkc2LAq32wCqZ1oW6aioY?si=e40a1d7069354c6a&#038;utm_source=oembed"></iframe></p><p> Later in the interview, Jamil recalled to Faith how she also saw her partner <a href="/artists/james-blake">James Blake</a> perform at last year&#39;s event, and explained how he helped her realise that she had “really checked out of life” when going through the grief.</p><p> “I tend to not register emotions in my brain – I just push emotions down into my body,” she added. “I rarely know I&#39;m depressed when I&#39;m depressed.”</p><p> This isn&#39;t the first time that Jamil has been open about her struggles. Last year <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/jameela-jamil-reveals-how-she-destroyed-her-body-with-laxatives-amid-anorexia-struggles-3761387">the <em>She-Hulk</em> star also spoke candidly about her battle with anorexia, explaining how taking laxatives “destroyed” her body.</a></p><p> She made the comments during an episode of Kelly Ripa&#39;s podcast <em><a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/jameela-jamil-would-choose-the-bear/id1676166337?i=1000657117072">Let&#39;s Talk Off Camera</a></em> , and shared the upsetting toll it took on her health.</p><p> “I fucked up my kidney, my liver, my digestive system, my heart. And most recently, I found out that I have destroyed my bone density,” she said. </p><figure id="attachment_2554824" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2554824" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-2554824 size-full" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712.jpg" alt="James Blake and Jameela Jamil" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1156175712-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2554824" class="wp-caption-text"> James Blake and Jameela Jamil. CREDIT: Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> “I&#39;m so sorry to my body that I have jeopardised my future so severely for a beauty standard and to try to fit in with other people… That&#39;s why I&#39;m so annoying, publicly, about eating disorders and diets. Because there&#39;s so much talk about the dangers of being in a bigger body and there&#39;s almost no talk about the dangers of not eating enough, only eating too much.”</p><p> As for Coldplay, <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/coldplay-glastonbury-2024-live-review-photos-setlist-3770486">the band&#39;s headline set at Glasto 2024 was given a four-star review from <em>NME</em></a> which read: “The best Glasto sets are you know you&#39;re witnessing one for the books, which is why it&#39;s a shame that such a monumental moment was closed with something of a shrug.</p><p> “It&#39;s not a slight on the simmering electro-pop subtlety of new single &#39;feelslikeimfallinginlove&#39; – it&#39;s lovely – but it&#39;s barely over a week old and Glasto were geared up for a more familiar full-stop,” it added. “In the words of the great Michael J Fox: “I guess you guys aren&#39;t ready for that yet.” </p><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lily-allen-speaks-out-on-time-in-treatment-centre-for-emotional-turmoil-after-david-harbour-split-3838153"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><h2><b>有关心理健康的帮助和建议：</b></h2><ul><li><a href="https://www.thecalmzone.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>冷静 - 反对生活的运动</b></a></li><li><a href="https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Help Musicians UK – Around the clock mental health support and advice for musicians</b></a> <b>(CALL MUSIC MINDS MATTER ON: 0808 802 8008)</b></li><li> <a href="http://www.musicsupport.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Music Support Org – Help and support for musicians struggling with alcoholism, addiction, or mental health issues</b></a> <b>(CALL: 0800 030 6789)</b></li><li> <a href="http://www.youngminds.org.uk/?gclid=CIuC-9ye69ICFQYo0wodX48KPA" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>年轻人 - 年轻人的健康和福祉的声音</b></a></li><li><a href="https://www.time-to-change.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Time To Change – Let&#39;s end mental health discrimination</b></a></li><li> <a href="http://www.samaritans.org/how-we-can-help-you/contact-us?gclid=CKyDztKf69ICFSIo0wodYjYL5A" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>撒玛利亚人 - 每天24小时机密支持</b></a></li></ul></div></div><p>The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jameela-jamil-on-how-she-ruined-glastonbury-for-coldplay-superfan-benedict-cumberbatch-3838706">Jameela Jamil on how she “ruined” Glastonbury for Coldplay superfan Benedict Cumberbatch</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
